Which two actions should be taken when the Workspace ONE UEM console is rendering text and diagrams incorrectly? (Choose two.)

choices.D: Check the Workspace ONE UEM DB version to match with the Console server.
choices.A: Run lisreset.exe and check that the IIS service is running.
choices.E: Stop all Workspace ONE services except the AirWatch Diagnostic Service.
choices.C: Reboot the Workspace ONE SQL server.
choices.B: Ensure that the Workspace ONE Device Services server has a newer version than the console server.

discussion.content:
Answer is A

questions.question_text:
An administrator has enabled Kerberos Constrained Delegation (KCD) on the SEG v2. If the administrator publishes a profile without a certificate payload and the user enters the password, everything works fine. When the user publishes the same profile with a certificate payload, the system is unable to connect and synchronize emails.
Which two troubleshooting steps need to be taken? (Choose two.)

choices.B: Verify if the service account is a member of the IIS user group on each CAS Exchange server.
choices.A: KCD is not supported on SEG v2.
choices.E: Verify that the service account is set to the service type OWA.
choices.C: Verify that the Workspace UEM Console certificate is uploaded as a client certificate chain.
choices.D: Verify that port 88 is not blocked between the SEG and the Active Directory domain controller(s).

discussion.content:
Answer: B, D
Page 5:
"Source | Port | Protocol | Destination
SEG 88 LDAP\kerberos Domain Controller"
Page 8:
